### 2. Module Lattice + NIST and Brainpool Curves Composites in OpenPGP
* **Presenter**: Stefan Ubbink
* **Slides**: [Module Lattice + NIST and Brainpool Curves Composites in OpenPGP (draft-ietf-openpgp-nist-bp-comp)](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-openpgp-module-lattice-nist-and-brainpool-curves-composites-in-openpgp-draft-ietf-openpgp-nist-bp-comp-00)
* **Relevant Draft**: `draft-ietf-openpgp-nist-bp-comp`
* Stefan Ubbink provided an update on PQ/C composites (ML-KEM and ML-DSA) combined with NIST and Brainpool curves. 
* Two independent and interoperable implementations have been successfully developed: one in `rnp` (experimental flag) and one in `sequoia-pgp`.
* The draft is technically stable and straightfowardly adds PQ/C with NIST/Brainpool curve code points to RFC 9980.
* Stefan Ubbink requested a Working Group Last Call (WGLC).

